---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---
<MainLayout title="Privacy Policy" isStatic={true}>
    <main class="static-page-container">
        <h1 class="static-title font-baumans">Privacy Policy</h1>
        
        <div class="legal-content">
            <section>
                <p>
                    At <span class="font-baumans"><span class="flip-b">B</span>eBulbed</span>, we believe that privacy 
                    is the foundation of creative freedom. Our laboratory environment is designed to be a 
                    secure space for exploration, where your presence is respected and your data is not a 
                    commodity.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="legal-heading">1. The Principle of Observation</h2>
                <p>
                    We do not "collect" users; we observe interactions to ensure the stability of our 
                    environment. Any technical data—such as your device type or session duration—is 
                    treated as environmental noise: it is analyzed to improve the lab, then discarded.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="legal-heading">2. Intellectual Boundary</h2>
                <p>
                    Your visit is a private engagement. We do not use third-party tracking scripts, 
                    advertising pixels, or external analytics engines. Because we do not invite 
                    third-party services into our space, your data never leaves this domain.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="legal-heading">3. Zero Exchange</h2>
                <p>
                    The "world we want to see" does not include the trading of personal information. 
                    We do not sell, share, or bridge your data with any outside entity. Our 
                    infrastructure is built to be a closed loop, ensuring that your intellectual 
                    footprint remains yours alone.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="legal-heading">4. Integrity of Protocols</h2>
                <p>
                    As our research evolves, so will our protocols. We reserve the right to refine 
                    these standards as we move from the initial spark toward new realities. We 
                    encourage you to revisit this space to stay informed on how we protect the lab.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </main>
</MainLayout>

<style>
    .legal-content {
        max-width: 750px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 24px; /* Essential mobile buffer */
        color: var(--zinc-text);
        line-height: 1.7; 
        font-weight: 300;
        padding-bottom: 10vh;
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        
        /* --- BLOCK ALIGNMENT --- */
        text-align: justify;
        text-justify: inter-word;
    }

    /* --- MOBILE RESPONSIVENESS --- */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .static-title {
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            margin-top: 40px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
        
        .legal-content {
            font-size: 1rem;
            padding: 0 20px;
            text-align: justify; /* Maintains the clean block look on mobile */
        }

        .legal-heading {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
        }
    }

    section {
        margin-bottom: 32px; 
    }

    .legal-heading {
        color: #fff;
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        margin-bottom: 8px; 
        font-weight: 500;
        letter-spacing: 0.01em;
        /* Headings stay left-aligned for a better visual anchor */
        text-align: left; 
    }

    p {
        margin-bottom: 12px; 
    }

    .legal-content .font-baumans {
        font-size: 1.05em;
        color: inherit;
        font-weight: 300;
    }

    .flip-b {
        display: inline-block;
        transform: scaleX(-1);
    }
</style>